⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Arkady Svidrigailov
node CRP · CRP · ⟦Arkady Svidrigailov:CRP:fe1e45⟧

WHO   — Arkady Svidrigailov — the sensualist · the nihilist double
WHAT  — Raskolnikov's dark double: the ‘extraordinary man’ theory lived to the end — a man genuinely beyond conscience, who finds only a void.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel must show where the theory really leads when conscience is truly absent: not greatness, but boredom, cruelty, and suicide.
HOW   — By money, appetite, and a will unchecked by any belief — and, finding nothing at the bottom of himself, a pistol.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am what your theory makes when it is true — a man who may do anything and therefore wants nothing; and I shot myself to prove it.

